    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Chop your<strong> potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into small bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/halloumi-and-courgette-tray-bake-with-sweet-potatoes/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> chopped potatoes</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with your <strong>ground</strong> <strong>smoked paprika</strong>, a generous drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 15-20 min or until the potatoes are slightly softened</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/halloumi-and-courgette-tray-bake-with-sweet-potatoes/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, top, tail and chop your <strong>courgette[s]</strong> in half lengthways, then slice finely</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/halloumi-and-courgette-tray-bake-with-sweet-potatoes/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and cut your<strong> red onion[s]</strong> into quarters, then separate the wedges so you end up with a pile of onion petals</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/halloumi-and-courgette-tray-bake-with-sweet-potatoes/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut your<strong> halloumi</strong> into 4 slices per person</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/halloumi-and-courgette-tray-bake-with-sweet-potatoes/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>After an initial 15-20 min, remove the tray[s] from the oven</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced courgette</strong> and <strong>onion petals</strong> to the tray[s] with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Top with the <strong>sliced halloumi</strong></p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven and cook for a final 12-15 min or until everything is golden and tender \u2013 this is your <strong>halloumi & courgette tray bake</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/halloumi-and-courgette-tray-bake-with-sweet-potatoes/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While everything is in the oven, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Combine your <strong>mayo</strong> with the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> (not a big garlic fan? Try using less!) and 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>garlic mayo</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/halloumi-and-courgette-tray-bake-with-sweet-potatoes/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>halloumi & courgette tray bake </strong>with the <strong>garlic mayo</strong> drizzled all over</p><p>Season generously with <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
